******************
		CNRS THEMATIC SCHOOL: BDA MDD
		19 - 24 June 2022, Bastia, Corsica, France=20
              https://cedric.cnam.fr/lab/confs/mdd2022/

*************************    REGISTRATION IS OPEN       =
***************************************
Inscription deadline: 15 mai 2022
The number of attendees is limited (priority will be given to PhD =
students) =20

Come to surf the waves of data with us!
=
**************************************************************************=
******************

The era of data is not over. Data integration, analytics, and modelling =
solutions should run on top of different target architectures in a =
data-driven society and environment. Database solutions, protocols and =
technology are evolving at a high pace, and this opens exciting =
challenges to be addressed through research and development approaches.=20=


The CNRS MDD thematic school "Masses of distributed data" is a recurrent =
thematic school taking place every two years since 2010. This school is =
an emanation of the database community in France, structured around the =
BDA conference: Data Management - Principles and Applications, which =
celebrated its 30th anniversary in 2016. If our conference is the =
meeting place of our community, the MDD thematic school allows us to =
expose in detail fundamental themes for the understanding of the =
evolution of our research field, and to prepare PhD students to follow - =
and provoke - its evolutions.

The MDD school has focused on themes related to these challenges in its =
first five sessions. The first session (2010) dealt with distributed =
data management systems and the Semantic Web; the second session (2012) =
focused on query processing operators at the Petabyte scale, new =
information sources (social networks), and the integration of data from =
independent environments; the 2014 session was dedicated to analytical =
data visualization, data quality, and crowdsourcing; and the 2016 =
session focused on integrated privacy-friendly processes for massive =
data analysis. In 2018, the session covered "Scalable Data Analytics" =
with ways to analyze data at large scale. The 2020 session was =
unfortunately suspended during the pandemic and postponed to 2022.=20

The MDD school will provide an intensive and exciting program and =
working environment with expert scientists who will lecture and practice =
the problems driving the domain. Scientific activities will be combined =
by informal discussion and activities that will promote the emergence of =
ideas, projects and experiments that will help PhD students and =
researchers complement their current research.=20

------- PROGRAM -------

6/19: Sunday afternoon : arrival

6/20: Monday : 	Heterogeneous Data Integration: Semantics and Polystores
		Ioana Manolescu, Fran=C3=A7ois Goasdou=C3=A9, Maxime =
Buron

6/21: Tuesday : 	Morning: Big Graph Processing Systems
				 Angela Bonifati, Chao Zhang

			Afternoon: How to conduct experiments?=20
				   Nicolas Travers

6/22: Wednesday : Morning : Deploying Deep Learning applications at =
scale: the database challenge=20
			    Genoveva Vargas-Solar and Javier Espinosa    =
                           =20
                 =20
		  Afternoon : Social event

6/23: Thursday : Data Security and Privacy for Outsourced Data in the =
Cloud
		 Amr el Abbadi, Tristan Allard

		Tutorial in the morning and practical session in the =
afternoon

6/24: Friday : Departure in the morning

The target audience of this school consists primarily of young =
researchers in the field of databases as well as in related or =
multidisciplinary fields (management of large amounts of data for =
scientific applications for example). By young researchers, we mean =
doctoral and post-doctoral students. The school is also open to more =
experienced teachers/researchers with the aim of thematic opening, the =
creation of an exchange network or retraining. The school is obviously =
aimed at research engineers from the private sector (R&D, startup, =
etc.).


