&nbsp; &nbsp;REGISTRATION IS OPEN &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =
***************************************</div><div class=3D"">Inscription =
deadline: 15 mai 2022</div><div class=3D"">The number of attendees is =
limited (priority will be given to PhD students) &nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">Come to surf the waves =
of data with us!</div><div =
class=3D"">***************************************************************=
*****************************</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">The era of data is not over. Data =
integration, analytics, and modelling solutions should run on top of =
different target architectures in a data-driven society and environment. =
Database solutions, protocols and technology are evolving at a high =
pace, and this opens exciting challenges to be addressed through =
research and development approaches.&nbsp;</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">The CNRS MDD thematic school "Masses of =
distributed data" is a recurrent thematic school taking place every two =
years since 2010. This school is an emanation of the database community =
in France, structured around the BDA conference: Data Management - =
Principles and Applications, which celebrated its 30th anniversary in =
2016. If our conference is the meeting place of our community, the MDD =
thematic school allows us to expose in detail fundamental themes for the =
understanding of the evolution of our research field, and to prepare PhD =
students to follow - and provoke - its evolutions.</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">The MDD school has =
focused on themes related to these challenges in its first five =
sessions. The first session (2010) dealt with distributed data =
management systems and the Semantic Web; the second session (2012) =
focused on query processing operators at the Petabyte scale, new =
information sources (social networks), and the integration of data from =
independent environments; the 2014 session was dedicated to analytical =
data visualization, data quality, and crowdsourcing; and the 2016 =
session focused on integrated privacy-friendly processes for massive =
data analysis. In 2018, the session covered "Scalable Data Analytics" =
with ways to analyze data at large scale. The 2020 session was =
unfortunately suspended during the pandemic and postponed to =
2022.&nbsp;</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">The =
MDD school will provide an intensive and exciting program and working =
environment with expert scientists who will lecture and practice the =
problems driving the domain. Scientific activities will be combined by =
informal discussion and activities that will promote the emergence of =
ideas, projects and experiments that will help PhD students and =
researchers complement their current research.&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">------- PROGRAM =
